photo.title: The Tale of 50 California and a Maple

description._content: The office tower is located in San Francisco's Financial District. Here 50 California Street is seen from the upper deck of EC2 (Embarcadero Center 2) on a warm July afternoon. I'm not sure but I think the tree in the foreground is a Maple. According to Wikipedia, the 37 story, 487 feet (148 m) tower was completed in 1972 and designed by architects Welton Becket & Associates.
